    "rationale": "The credibility assessment package is accepted for submission as a synthetic adversarial test case. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been evaluated; 7 assessed factors show achieved levels below required levels and 6 factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 5 epistemic gaps. The provenance chain from the primary claim includes a multi-hop path through the PIV validation result to a foundational FDA dataset. A second validation result (hemolysis-index-scalar-comparison) references an intermediate evidence node (prior-external-hemolysis-invitro-result) that carries no upstream prov:wasDerivedFrom, prov:wasGeneratedBy, or prov:used edge and is not marked uofa:isFoundationalEvidence: true, instantiating W-PROV-01. The description of that node states it is derived from prior experimental work without an IRI link, which may appear plausible on quick review.",
